#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an5.74"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an5.74:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 5 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 5 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.74:0.2"
msgid "8. Yodhājīvavagga "
msgstr "8. Warriors "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an5.74:0.3"
msgid "74. Dutiyadhammavihārīsutta "
msgstr "74. One Who Lives by the Teaching (2nd) "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.88, sc1
msgctxt "an5.74:1.1"
msgid "Atha kho aññataro bhikkhu yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho so bhikkhu bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then a mendicant went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and said to him: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.74:1.2"
msgid "“‘dhammavihārī, dhammavihārī’ti, bhante, vuccati. "
msgstr "“Sir, they speak of ‘one who lives by the teaching’. "

msgctxt "an5.74:1.3"
msgid "Kittāvatā nu kho, bhante, bhikkhu dhammavihārī hotī”ti? "
msgstr "How is one who lives by the teaching defined?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "an5.74:2.1"
msgid "“Idha, bhikkhu, bhikkhu dhammaṃ pariyāpuṇāti—"
msgstr "“Mendicant, take a mendicant who memorizes the teaching—"

msgctxt "an5.74:2.2"
msgid "suttaṃ, geyyaṃ, veyyākaraṇaṃ, gāthaṃ, udānaṃ, itivuttakaṃ, jātakaṃ, abbhutadhammaṃ, vedallaṃ; "
msgstr "statements, songs, discussions, verses, inspired exclamations, legends, stories of past lives, amazing stories, and classifications. "

#. VAR: uttari cassa → uttariñcassa (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "an5.74:2.3"
msgid "uttari cassa paññāya atthaṃ nappajānāti. "
msgstr "But they don’t understand the higher meaning. "

msgctxt "an5.74:2.4"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhu: ‘bhikkhu pariyattibahulo, no dhammavihārī’. "
msgstr "That mendicant is called one who studies a lot, not one who lives by the teaching. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "an5.74:3.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhu, bhikkhu yathāsutaṃ yathāpariyattaṃ dhammaṃ vitthārena paresaṃ deseti, uttari cassa paññāya atthaṃ nappajānāti. "
msgstr "Furthermore, a mendicant teaches Dhamma in detail to others as they learned and memorized it. But they don’t understand the higher meaning. "

msgctxt "an5.74:3.2"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhu: ‘bhikkhu paññattibahulo, no dhammavihārī’. "
msgstr "That mendicant is called one who advocates a lot, not one who lives by the teaching. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "an5.74:4.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhu, bhikkhu yathāsutaṃ yathāpariyattaṃ dhammaṃ vitthārena sajjhāyaṃ karoti, uttari cassa paññāya atthaṃ nappajānāti. "
msgstr "Furthermore, a mendicant recites the teaching in detail as they learned and memorized it. But they don’t understand the higher meaning. "

msgctxt "an5.74:4.2"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhu: ‘bhikkhu sajjhāyabahulo, no dhammavihārī’. "
msgstr "That mendicant is called one who recites a lot, not one who lives by the teaching. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "an5.74:5.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhu, bhikkhu yathāsutaṃ yathāpariyattaṃ dhammaṃ cetasā anuvitakketi anuvicāreti manasānupekkhati, uttari cassa paññāya atthaṃ nappajānāti. "
msgstr "Furthermore, a mendicant thinks about and considers the teaching in their heart, examining it with the mind as they learned and memorized it. But they don’t understand the higher meaning. "

msgctxt "an5.74:5.2"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhu: ‘bhikkhu vitakkabahulo, no dhammavihārī’. "
msgstr "That mendicant is called one who thinks a lot, not one who lives by the teaching. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "an5.74:6.1"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhu, bhikkhu dhammaṃ pariyāpuṇāti—"
msgstr "Take a mendicant who memorizes the teaching—"

msgctxt "an5.74:6.2"
msgid "suttaṃ, geyyaṃ, veyyākaraṇaṃ, gāthaṃ, udānaṃ, itivuttakaṃ, jātakaṃ, abbhutadhammaṃ, vedallaṃ; "
msgstr "statements, songs, discussions, verses, inspired exclamations, legends, stories of past lives, amazing stories, and classifications. "

msgctxt "an5.74:6.3"
msgid "uttari cassa paññāya atthaṃ pajānāti. "
msgstr "And they do understand the higher meaning. "

msgctxt "an5.74:6.4"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhu, bhikkhu dhammavihārī hoti. "
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant is one who lives by the teaching. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.89, sc7
msgctxt "an5.74:7.1"
msgid "Iti kho, bhikkhu, desito mayā pariyattibahulo, desito paññattibahulo, desito sajjhāyabahulo, desito vitakkabahulo, desito dhammavihārī. "
msgstr "So, mendicant, I’ve taught you the one who studies a lot, the one who advocates a lot, the one who recites a lot, the one who thinks a lot, and the one who lives by the teaching. "

msgctxt "an5.74:7.2"
msgid "Yaṃ kho, bhikkhu, satthārā karaṇīyaṃ sāvakānaṃ hitesinā anukampakena anukampaṃ upādāya, kataṃ vo taṃ mayā. "
msgstr "Out of compassion, I’ve done what a teacher should do who wants what’s best for their disciples. "

msgctxt "an5.74:7.3"
msgid "Etāni, bhikkhu, rukkhamūlāni, etāni suññāgārāni. Jhāyatha bhikkhu, mā pamādattha, mā pacchā vippaṭisārino ahuvattha. Ayaṃ vo amhākaṃ anusāsanī”ti. "
msgstr "Here are these roots of trees, and here are these empty huts. Practice absorption, mendicant! Don’t be negligent! Don’t regret it later! This is my instruction to you.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an5.74:7.4"
msgid "Catutthaṃ. "
msgstr ""

